added.title: New Chum
added.description: To prove he is extreme, Robotman becomes friends with King Shark and his gang of suckerfish.

added.title: Putting Together The Pieces
added.description: The journey begins to the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: Heart of the Forest Finale
added.description: The epic finale of the quest for the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: Dial B for Birder
added.description: Harold uncovers a secret plot that Chef's new parrot is hatching and tries to save his teacher only to discover that Sugar figured it out before him. Or did she?

added.title: A Hole Lot of Trouble
added.description: When rain derails an outside game of catch someone suggests they play it inside. This prompts Izzy to lead the group through her wildly imaginative worst case scenario. It's an adventure so scary that the kids many never play again.

added.title: A Tall Tale
added.description: After Owen's BBF, Noah, goes through a growth spurt, Owen fears losing his friend and takes drastic action.

added.title: A Dingo Ate My Duncan
added.description: When all their classmates are replaced with well behaved Australian doppelgangers in a school exchange program, Lightning and Cody start getting suspicious.

added.title: Teacher, Soldier, Chef, Spy
added.description: When Beth, Duncan and Izzy break Chef's new VR helmet they have to recreate his game world to keep him from ever finding out the truth.

added.title: Out to Launch
added.description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: Ben 10,000
added.description: Ben gets sucked into the future by a grown up Gwen. His mission is to help the now all powerful and adult Ben 10,000 seemingly defeat the future versions of Dr. Animo and Vilgax. However, the real reason Ben has been brought to the future is to teach his adult self some humility and the fact he's lost touch with Max and has forgotten what's really important, family.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: What a Night for a Knight
added.description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

added.title: Mystery 101
added.description: Velma's got an interview at the prestigious Kingston University, the most selective school in the country. The only catch? The dean wants her and the rest of the Scooby gang to figure out why the ghost of Elias Kingston, the school's founder, is haunting Kingston's book-filled halls!

added.title: What a Night for a Dark Knight!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang come to Gotham City to visit Alfred Pennyworth, they stumble into a dangerous mystery! Alfred's been kidnapped by the Man-Bat! Batman is on the case and he does not want any help from our meddling kids.

added.title: Beware the Beast from Below
added.description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

added.title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
added.description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

added.title: Game of Chicken
added.description: Fred gets a call for help from Chuck, his daredevil of a best friend, leading the gang on a rescue mission deep in the caverns of an ancient civilization. Once there, they learn of the real mystery: the ghost of the Tribal Warrior still protects the cavern from outsiders!

added.title: The Creeping Creatures
added.description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

added.title: Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are taking a tour of merry old London, they run afoul of horrible screaming skulls of English legend! They team up with an eccentric man who claims to be none other than Sherlock Holmes. Of course, he can't be the real thing, can he?

added.title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
added.description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

added.title: A Mystery Solving Gang Divided!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang travel to Chambersburg, a battlefield near Gettysburg, to investigate the mysterious appearance of ghost zombie Civil War soldiers and come face to face with a rival mystery solving gang, the Funky Phantom crew. The rivalry between the two gangs gets so out of hand that it threatens to keep either group from solving the mystery, until the ghost of Abraham Lincoln appears and tries to get them focused.

added.title: All Paws on Deck
added.description: The gang climb aboard the cruise ship run by Fred's cousin, despite Velma's strong dislike of water. But a water phobia is the least of their problems when a terrifying sea monster attacks the ship!

added.title: Hassle in the Castle
added.description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

added.title: Poodle Justice
added.description: It's Scooby's dream come true as the gang visits the set of his favorite TV show and he meets the star, his celebrity crush, a dog actress who plays a detective on the screen. Now all Scooby has to do is work up the courage to actually talk to her while also solving the mystery of the monstrous gargoyle attacking the production!

added.title: Revenge of the Swamp Monster!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang meet up with basketball legend and bowling aficionado Chris Paul at a golf tournament fundraiser held in Florida. Shaggy's come to caddy for Mr. Paul and help him with this game so the Assist King can save a local school from going under. But, when a horrible Swamp Monster attacks trying to destroy the charity event, our heroes and Mr. Paul must finish the tournament and save the school, and possibly their own lives!

added.title: Mine Your Own Business
added.description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

added.title: Revenge of the Man Crab
added.description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

added.title: The Song of Mystery
added.description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

added.title: Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!
added.description: Scooby and the Mystery Inc. gang meet Wanda Sykes, who is helping save a bunch of cute, fuzzy animals up for adoption in a large pet supply store. When a crazy monster egg hatches a monster in the pet store's back room, our heroes and Wanda must not only save the store and the animals, but their own lives!

added.title: Grand Scam
added.description: Shaggy takes the Gang to the Minor League Baseball stadium of his youth only to learn that it's about to be shut down because a Ghostly Baseball Player is scaring away the fans and the team! Shaggy puts aside his cowardly ways to saves his home team but will Scooby stand by his, now not so scared, pal?

added.title: Decoy for a Dognapper
added.description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Up in the Air
added.description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

added.title: Skate Park
added.description: The Looney Builders build a skate park for the kids, but it soon interferes with Hoots Talon and his friends' activities.

added.title: Batty Kathy
added.description: As The Looney Builders build Kathy Bat an upside-down radio station, Porky has concerns but doesn't speak up.

added.title: Percy in the Middle
added.description: After Gordon tells all the young engines that they have a day off to relax, Thomas and Diesel insist on a teamed relay race through the obstacle course. Percy is the only one who isn't interested in playing, so Thomas asks him to referee instead. He reluctantly agrees and the race is on! Coming to a split second finish, Percy determines Thomas' team wins, but Diesel doesn't accept and calls for a rematch. Once again the teams race and Diesel wins after accidentally causing an oil spill. Both teams become so angry with each other, they're too distracted when Percy runs off to chase butterflies. Thomas, Diesel, and friends finally notice Percy's absence and speed after him, but they'll need to learn their lesson about sportsmanship if they want to ensure this day off is a success.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Seeking a Safer Sodor
added.description: After a near-collision rattles their wheels, Percy and Kana enlist the help of Emily to introduce new safety measures all over Sodor. However, their anxiousness about accidents push Percy and Kana to ridiculous extremes that only makes more trouble! When Percy has another accident caused by his off-the-rails safety obsession, he refuses to leave Tidmouth Sheds. When he has to leap into action to help his friends, Percy learns that paying attention to your surroundings is the best way to not have an accident.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
added.description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

added.title: Yip Yip Tree Tree/The Snowman Scarecrow
added.description: When the ornaments on the Pretty Big City tree break, the Mechas must build new ones and save the holidays for their friends./It's time for Zee and MacBarm's gift exchange, but the snowman scarecrow Zee made for MacBarm keeps blowing away!

removed.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

removed.title: Camp Fear
removed.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

removed.title: The Unnaturals
removed.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

removed.title: Monster Weather
removed.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

removed.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
removed.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

removed.title: Do the Skeleton Dance - Halloween Special
removed.description: Lellobee City Farm learns to do the groovy Skeleton Dance for Halloween.

removed.description: When Snowy and Jestah team up to execute a mysterious plan involving rare freeze-berries, Batwing and Buff pair up to take on the dastardly duo, but Batwing decides to carry out the mission herself, putting both her and Buff at risk.

removed.title: Trick or Treat
removed.description: D.BO wonders what is trick-or-treating?

removed.title: Halloween Song
removed.description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Halloween Song"

removed.title: Taz Recycle
removed.description: When The Looney Builders build Taz a wrecking ball vehicle, he struggles to learn how to operate it.

removed.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
removed.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

removed.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
removed.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

removed.description: Blippi wonders how do you celebrate Dia De Los Muertos?

removed.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

removed.title: Halloween Party
removed.description: D.BO wonders how do you throw the best Halloween party ever?

removed.title: To the Batmobile!
removed.description: When all of the Batwheels (except for Bam) mysteriously disappear, Bam enlists the help of A.D.A.M, the original Batmobile, to help save his friends. removed.title: Party Boat
removed.description: The Looney Builders build a party boat for Mac and Tosh when Tweety accidentally makes a mistake but doesn't ask for help.

removed.title: Wheels on the Bus
removed.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

removed.title: Trick or Treat
removed.description: Mei, Mummy and Ella (3 generations of the same family) are all trick or treating together around the CITY!

removed.title: Scare Contest
removed.description: Blippi wonders is it really fun to be scared?

removed.title: Beware the Scare-Crow
removed.description: During a visit to the farm of Penny Bennyson's grandfather, Team Tennyson is constantly haunted by a Scare-Crow that's come to life, but when Ben discovers that Aristocrow is behind it all, our hero must defeat Aristocrow's master, the steam-powered Steam Smythe, if he is to save his cousin's farm!

removed.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
removed.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

removed.title: The Monsters in Your Head
removed.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

removed.title: Scared Silly
removed.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

removed.title: Gwen Scary, Gwen Lost
removed.description: When Chef discovers his spooky Halloween pranks have never scared the kids he's devastated. Determined to get them this year, he agrees to hand over full control of his pranking to Gwen. Her plan turns out far spookier then Chef ever hoped.

removed.title: Duncan Carving
removed.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

removed.title: Bearly Edible
removed.description: After eating the snacks meant for everyone and replacing them with disgusting low budget cookies from Barfvomita, Owen is full of guilt (and cookies) and tries to make things right.

removed.title: Mad Math: Taffy Road
removed.description: After Courtney refuses to share her taffy winnings from a calculus for candy competition, she's transported to the desolate future where she learns that greed is not without consequence.

removed.title: Ghoul Spirit
removed.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.
